He certainly was right.
Could I blame her, hold her in contempt, even say that she was wrong?
No.
However, the end which conformed to the rule, to the truth, did not satisfy my poetic appetite.
These heroic deeds demand a beautiful sacrifice, which seemed to be lacking, and I felt a certain disappointment.
I suddenly asked: "Has Madame de Fleurel any children?"
"Yes, one girl and two boys.
It is for them that I am bringing these toys.
She and her husband are very kind to me."
