He is certainly always rather like a squirrel, but then every one of us has retained the type of some animal or other as the mark of his primitive origin.
How many people have jaws like a bulldog, or heads like goats, rabbits, foxes, horses, or oxen.
Paul is a squirrel turned into a man.
He has its bright, quick eyes, its hair, its pointed nose, its small, fine, supple, active body, and a certain mysterious resemblance in his general bearing; in fact, a similarity of movement, of gesture, and of bearing which might almost be taken for a recollection.
